      "type": "theory",
      "id": "theory_dec_to_hex",
      "title": "Converting Decimal to Hex",
      "content": "Converting decimal to hexadecimal uses the same principle as decimal to binary, but we divide by 16 instead of 2!\n\n**Division by 16 Method:**\n\n1. Divide the decimal number by 16\n2. Write down the remainder (0-15)\n3. If remainder is 10-15, convert to A-F\n4. Divide the quotient by 16\n5. Repeat until quotient is 0\n6. Read remainders from BOTTOM to TOP\n\n**Example 1: Convert 175 to hex**\n\n175 \u00f7 16 = 10 remainder 15 (F)\n10 \u00f7 16 = 0 remainder 10 (A)\n\nReading bottom to top: AF\nSo 175 in decimal = AF in hex!\n\n**Example 2: Convert 1000 to hex**\n\n1000 \u00f7 16 = 62 remainder 8\n62 \u00f7 16 = 3 remainder 14 (E)\n3 \u00f7 16 = 0 remainder 3\n\nReading bottom to top: 3E8\nSo 1000 in decimal = 3E8 in hex!\n\n**Conversion Table for Remainders:**\n0-9: Stay as digits 0-9\n10: A\n11: B\n12: C\n13: D\n14: E\n15: F\n\n**Useful Values to Know:**\n\u2022 15 = F\n\u2022 16 = 10\n\u2022 255 = FF (max byte value)\n\u2022 256 = 100\n\u2022 4095 = FFF\n\nRemember: When your remainder is 10 or more, convert it to the corresponding letter A-F!"
    },
